00:00:19,416 --> 00:00:21,666
Hello everyone!
Kaleido Star is about to begin.

2
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:23,291
While you're watching
Kaleido Star,

3
00:00:23,375 --> 00:00:25,250
make sure to keep
your room brightly lit,

4
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:27,458
and don't sit too
close to the telly!

5
00:00:27,541 --> 00:00:29,000
Cheers!

6
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:32,208
Well well well.
Rosetta here!

7
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:34,416
Did you guys see my trapeze act?

8
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,625
I was so excited to
perform with Sora.

9
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:40,000
I admire her so much.
I'm gonna train hard like Sora

10
00:00:40,083 --> 00:00:42,083
and become an even
better trapeze artist.

11
00:00:42,166 --> 00:00:45,000
I'm gonna give it another shot
during our next circus tour.

12
00:00:45,083 --> 00:00:49,291
I've met a very special person
on tour, and that person is...

13
00:00:49,375 --> 00:00:51,416
I'd better not give
it away just yet!

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,333
Let's perform
together again today!

15
00:00:53,416 --> 00:00:55,625
Let's, let's, let's!

16
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,000
But... uh...

17
00:02:31,083 --> 00:02:34,458
So that's the deal. I've even
gotten the boss's permission.

18
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:35,791
Hold on!

19
00:02:35,875 --> 00:02:38,666
I've gotta meet my mom,
so I'm heading out early.

20
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:41,208
Oh, oh yeah, that's right.

21
00:02:41,291 --> 00:02:44,000
Here are eight plane
tickets. Take 'em!

22
00:02:44,083 --> 00:02:45,250
Thanks, but I...

23
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:47,333
There's also some info
on where we're going.

24
00:02:47,416 --> 00:02:49,416
Uh, sure. But what do I...

25
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,458
Okay, see you in France.

26
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:55,041
Um... right.
See you in France.

27
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:59,125
In France!!

28
00:03:01,416 --> 00:03:03,833
Leon's Amazing Past.

29
00:03:10,291 --> 00:03:11,791
I get it.

30
00:03:11,875 --> 00:03:15,250
So she must have had her mother
Anne get all of this together.

31
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:18,666
I guess Mr. Kennth's show
sparked a fire in Rosetta.

32
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:21,708
Apparently the only condition
is she has to do Diabolo

33
00:03:21,791 --> 00:03:23,291
in the show that
Anne has planned.

34
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:26,666
So that's why she left a week
early, to practice Diabolo.

35
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:28,708
I can't speak for everyone,
but the Clown team

36
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:31,208
never dreamed of an
opportunity like this.

37
00:03:31,291 --> 00:03:32,875
Aren't you excited, Ken?

38
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:35,333
I'm not a clown right now,
I'm your manager.

39
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:37,291
You know, we haven't
been back to France

40
00:03:37,375 --> 00:03:39,000
since the circus festival.

41
00:03:39,083 --> 00:03:41,666
That's why we have to make sure
this trip is a happier one.

42
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:44,000
--That's right.
--Mm hmm.

43
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:45,541
Excuse me?

44
00:03:48,083 --> 00:03:49,833
Is she smiling?

45
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:51,958
How long are you going
to stand around chatting?

46
00:03:52,041 --> 00:03:53,666
You're wasting my time.

47
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:56,833
We should have known it
was too good to be true.

48
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:59,000
Follow me, I found
the taxi stand.

49
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:01,125
What would you kids do without
me?

50
00:04:01,208 --> 00:04:03,833
This'll be fun, let's go!

51
00:04:03,916 --> 00:04:05,500
Yeah...

52
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:08,708
I finally figured it out
at Mr. Kenneth's show.

53
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:11,916
When Sora performs,
she watches the audience.

54
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,708
I was always too busy
watching Sora or Leon perform.

55
00:04:15,791 --> 00:04:18,458
What Sora has that I've
been missing is the ability

56
00:04:18,541 --> 00:04:23,375
to please the audience. She has
the power to create smiles.

57
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:26,708
Now that I know her secret,
I can learn to do it as well.

58
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:30,875
All I have to do is get my own
smile back first.

59
00:04:30,958 --> 00:04:34,208
That's what Miss Layla was
trying to teach me.

60
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:38,625
Um... Um... Um...

61
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:42,375
Uh... Um... Um... cirque noir?

62
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:43,958
Ah, oui mademoiselle.

63
00:04:44,041 --> 00:04:45,875
Oh good, I think
he understands me!

64
00:04:45,958 --> 00:04:49,416
Well we have to take two taxis,
so I hope you can do it again.

65
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:54,125
Nous? Um... allez, cirque noir?

66
00:04:56,375 --> 00:04:58,416
Time to wake up Mr. Cabbie!

67
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,708
I know the French like to nap,

68
00:04:59,791 --> 00:05:02,375
but you've got customers
waiting on you.

69
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:06,041
Oui oui mademoiselle!

70
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:14,333
I welcome you to the
Noir Circus, Miss Rosetta.

71
00:05:14,416 --> 00:05:15,958
Thanks, I'm very excited.

72
00:05:16,041 --> 00:05:17,583
The others should
be arriving soon.

73
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:20,583
Do you think it'd be okay
if I wait here for them, sir?

74
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:23,125
Of course!
Make yourself at home.

75
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:26,291
I was wondering... I don't
suppose you'd be interested

76
00:05:26,375 --> 00:05:27,958
in doing a little
Diabolo performance

77
00:05:28,041 --> 00:05:30,916
in our show starting tomorrow?

78
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,208
I could, but I'd have
to charge extra.

79
00:05:34,291 --> 00:05:36,666
In the deal that was worked out,
you were able to contract

80
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:40,083
former top star Sora Naegino and
circus festival winner May Wong

81
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:42,125
at one low price.
The only condition was

82
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:44,208
that you had to cast me
as a trapeze artist.

83
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:45,625
So Diabolo would
be an extra fee.

84
00:05:45,708 --> 00:05:47,708
Alright, that is
enough, I get it.

85
00:05:47,791 --> 00:05:50,458
Just pretend we never
had this conversation.

86
00:05:51,958 --> 00:05:55,125
I may be inexperienced, but
I've been training really hard.

87
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:59,083
I promise, I won't disappoint
you or the audience, sir.

88
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:01,416
I've got high hopes for you.

89
00:06:03,666 --> 00:06:06,041
That is our star, René.

90
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:15,625
Wow, that was an awesome move!

91
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,958
Looks like you're in
top form today René.

92
00:06:18,041 --> 00:06:20,291
No different than any other day.

93
00:06:20,375 --> 00:06:21,833
Hey!

94
00:06:21,916 --> 00:06:24,250
--Allez.
--Not you again.

95
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:28,208
Don't get so angry,
I'll be leaving soon.

96
00:06:28,291 --> 00:06:29,541
Huh?

97
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:32,041
I thought I asked you
not to come here anymore.

98
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:33,458
That's not very nice.

99
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:36,083
Do not forget everything
I taught you.

100
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:39,000
I haven't been your
student for a long time.

101
00:06:39,083 --> 00:06:41,791
You see, the thing is,
I've run out of cash.

102
00:06:41,875 --> 00:06:45,000
You need money to buy alcohol?

103
00:06:45,083 --> 00:06:49,666
You know me all too well, uh?
This will be the last time.

104
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:53,916
Ridiculous.

105
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:58,000
Merci René, I'll stop by
to pay you, I promise.

106
00:06:58,083 --> 00:06:59,375
I don't want your money.

107
00:06:59,458 --> 00:07:02,333
Just promise you won't
come back here again.

108
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:06,166
You're so generous.
So long, René.

109
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,750
I can't believe him.

110
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,083
Who was that man?

111
00:07:11,166 --> 00:07:12,666
That's Alan Rubel.

112
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:16,000
He used to be the best trainer
of trapeze artists in the world.

113
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:17,875
Trapeze artist?!

114
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:20,666
Alan was what you'd call
a freelance trainer.

115
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,541
He'd scout kids who
seemed to have talent

116
00:07:22,625 --> 00:07:25,541
and train them to be
first class trapeze artists.

117
00:07:25,625 --> 00:07:27,708
He trained many of
the world's finest.

118
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:30,541
In fact, René was
one of his students.

119
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:32,916
His skill as a trainer
was world-renowned,

120
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,916
but he quit several years ago.

121
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,250
You've seen what
he has become now.

122
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:40,416
A world-renowned trainer
of trapeze artists.

123
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:44,583
Hey, Rosetta!

124
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,458
Excuse me!

125
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:55,541
My name's Rosetta, and I'm
from Kaleido Stage.

126
00:07:55,625 --> 00:07:58,125
Please, I want you to
teach me the trapeze!

127
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:01,083
I promise I'll work
really hard, please sir!

128
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,583
Hey, wait!

129
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:07,083
So you're the Kaleido
people? You're late!

130
00:08:07,166 --> 00:08:09,916
What? But doesn't the
show start tomorrow?

131
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,291
What are you talking about?!

132
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:13,541
We'll start rehearsal
immédiatement.

133
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:14,833
Okay.

134
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:16,500
Following me won't
do you any good.

135
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:19,500
Sorry, but I'm not giving up
until you teach me the trapeze.

136
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:41,875
This is... This is a
circus training area!

137
00:08:41,958 --> 00:08:45,583
Right now it is nothing
but a room full of junk.

138
00:08:45,666 --> 00:08:47,458
Can I get on the trapeze?

139
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:08,041
You're not very good at it.

140
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:10,000
Kaleido Stage must be slipping

141
00:09:10,083 --> 00:09:13,541
if they are letting amateurs
like you on stage.

142
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,125
Don't talk bad about
the Kaleido Stage.

143
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:43,250
I'm only learning the trapeze
because I want to.

144
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:47,500
I have to say,
that's pretty impressive.

145
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:50,208
You're a strange girl,
but you've got talent.

146
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:52,208
What's going on?!

147
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:55,416
Sora! Hey, nobody
told us about this!

148
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:58,875
Don't be silly. This has always
been our main attraction.

149
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:00,166
You must be joking!

150
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:02,166
Trois, deux, allez!

151
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:04,583
Help me!

152
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,875
Wait a minute, put those down!

153
00:10:08,958 --> 00:10:10,500
I don't wanna die!

154
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:20,041
Brilliant!

155
00:10:20,125 --> 00:10:23,875
So umm... this is the
Noir Circus, right?

156
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:27,250
No, this is the Etoile Circus.

157
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:29,333
Sorry we're late.
We're the Kaleido Planets.

158
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:31,833
We're scheduled
to perform today.

159
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:33,833
 Excuse me?!

160
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,791
I thought I was about to die.

161
00:10:35,875 --> 00:10:39,541
Sure it wasn't what we expected,
but wasn't it thrilling?

162
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:43,250
Welcome to Noir Circus.
We have been expecting you.

163
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,750
I'm so sorry we're late.

164
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:47,250
We're the touring team
from Kaleido Stage.

165
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,625
Has our friend
Rosetta arrived yet?

166
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:52,958
Yes, she is here, but I think
she may be over at Alan's place.

167
00:10:53,041 --> 00:10:54,500
Alan?

168
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:10,250
What's the matter?
You are ready to quit?

169
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:14,458
I won't. Sora never gave up
on Leon's special training.

170
00:11:14,541 --> 00:11:16,166
--Huh?
--I won't give up.

171
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:19,458
Leon? Are you talking
about Leon Oswald?

172
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:21,166
Yeah, that's him.

173
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,583
How do you know him?

174
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:26,666
He's performing with the Kaleido
Stage. So you know Leon?

175
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:30,291
I know him well.
He was the last student

176
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:32,708
I ever trained on the trapeze.

177
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,875
Bonjour!

178
00:11:35,958 --> 00:11:38,291
Hello? Is there anyone here?

179
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:39,791
Sora!

180
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:41,333
Rosetta!

181
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:44,083
Sora?

182
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:57,625
You taught Leon the trapeze?

183
00:11:57,708 --> 00:11:59,875
Yes, it's been about 10 years

184
00:11:59,958 --> 00:12:03,875
since Leon and his little
sister Sophie trained here.

185
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:07,166
Little sister?

186
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:09,875
Their parents died when
they were both very young.

187
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:12,791
After that, they were
taken in by their relatives.

188
00:12:12,875 --> 00:12:15,666
But they must not have been
on good terms with them.

189
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:18,750
When I asked to take the two
of them in as my students,

190
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:21,666
their relatives were
eager to give them up.

191
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,958
They were brilliant students.

192
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:28,625
They mastered the basics of
the trapeze in no time at all.

193
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:36,083
Now Leon! Pull Sophie up
and throw her into the air!

194
00:12:41,125 --> 00:12:44,250
No good! Start again
from the beginning!

195
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,041
Oh, Leon.

196
00:12:48,125 --> 00:12:52,041
So was Sophie really capable
of being Leon's partner?

197
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:55,750
Yes. In fact, in my opinion,

198
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:59,875
Leon wasn't talented enough
to be Sophie's partner.

199
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:02,041
She was more talented than Leon?

200
00:13:02,125 --> 00:13:04,166
I didn't think
that was possible.

201
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:07,666
I think Sophie would have
been able to do it one day.

202
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:10,583
A "Perfect Angel's Maneuver."

203
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:13,458
The "Angel's Maneuver"?

204
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:17,041
Yes. That was my dream.

205
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:20,916
I assumed, to perform a
"Perfect Angel's Maneuver,"

206
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,916
the woman's partner needed
a lot of upper body strength.

207
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,375
So, I started training Leon.

208
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:32,291
You dropped the ball, kid.
Here, I'll get it for you.

209
00:13:32,375 --> 00:13:35,291
This ball, it's... made of lead!

210
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,875
However, no matter how
much I trained Leon,

211
00:13:40,958 --> 00:13:44,083
they still could not complete
an "Angel's Maneuver."

212
00:13:44,166 --> 00:13:46,041
That's when I began
to wonder if it was

213
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:48,208
an impossible goal for me.

214
00:13:52,583 --> 00:13:54,125
Sophie!

215
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:55,666
Leon!

216
00:13:57,625 --> 00:13:59,750
Then, Sophie pulled herself up

217
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:02,791
as if she were as
light as a feather.

218
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:06,250
When I saw that,
I finally understood.

219
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:11,041
The "Angel's Maneuver" did not
just require one strong partner.

220
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:15,166
It required that the other
partner have an innate instinct

221
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:18,916
to sense the flow of that
strength during a performance.

222
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:22,666
I figured if she could perfectly
maintain the pose,

223
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:26,750
then they could really achieve
a perfect "Angel's Maneuver."

224
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:31,000
That's when I decided to start
training Sophie harshly as well.

225
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:33,291
Sophie! Are you okay?

226
00:14:33,375 --> 00:14:35,166
Get off the stage!

227
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,625
I am sorry, Leon.

228
00:14:36,708 --> 00:14:38,208
We want our money back!

229
00:14:38,291 --> 00:14:41,833
My sister's been training and
she's tired! It's not her fault!

230
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:43,500
--Like I care!
--You brat!

231
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:45,708
Don't forget that you're
here to entertain us!

232
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:47,500
Yeah, quit mouthing off!

233
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:51,750
Alan, I am sorry, but I cannot
pay them their fee now.

234
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:53,708
You have to stop
the special training.

235
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:54,875
What did you say?

236
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:57,250
Sophie can't handle
much more of this.

237
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:58,666
It's okay, Leon.

238
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:02,166
Sophie? But are you
not exhausted?

239
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:04,666
Alan, do you know
about "True Stars"?

240
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:06,916
--Huh?
--"True Stars"?

241
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,500
Some people from
the circus troupe

242
00:15:08,583 --> 00:15:10,625
we were working with
told me about it.

243
00:15:10,708 --> 00:15:13,500
They told me that the
performance of a true star

244
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:16,833
brings everybody's
hearts together as one.

245
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:20,291
I think the "Angel's Maneuver"
could be the only way

246
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:23,375
for us to become
true stars someday.

247
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:27,041
Leon, I think that
we could do it.

